# Treblinka data:
library(tidyverse)
library(lubridate)
library(here)
rmdata <- 
  read_csv(here("content","post","2020-11-07-a-tutorial-on-bootstrap-confidence-interval","Treblinka.csv")) %>%
  mutate(date = as.Date(`Date`, '%b %d, %Y'),
         month = month(date),
         year = year(date),
         count = `Victims of Treblinka`,
         day = day(date),
         weekday = weekdays(date),
         obs = row_number(),
         cumCount = cumsum(count),) %>%
  dplyr::select(-c(Date,`Victims of Treblinka`)) %>% 
  # select(obs, date, count)%>%
  filter(!is.na(count)) %>% # remove missing data 
  arrange(date)
  
rmdata

The data set to analyze is the victim counts at the notorious Holocaust site at .

library(fitdistrplus)
x <- rmdata$count
model.nbinom <- fitdist(x, "nbinom", method = "mle", control = list(maxit = 5000))
# model.pois <- fitdist(x, "pois", method = "mle")

par(mfrow = c(1, 1))
# plot.legend <- c("Weibull", "lognormal", "gamma")
plot.legend <- c("nbinom")

summary(model.nbinom)
plot(model.nbinom)

plot(model.nbinom, demp = TRUE)
plot(model.nbinom, histo = FALSE, demp = TRUE)
denscomp(list( model.nbinom), legendtext = plot.legend)
qqcomp(list( model.nbinom), legendtext = plot.legend)
cdfcomp(list(model.nbinom), legendtext = plot.legend)
ppcomp(list(model.nbinom), legendtext = plot.legend)

prob <- seq(0,1,0.01)

x_vec <- seq(0,1000000, 1000)
vec1 <- rep(NA, 1001)
for (i in x_vec) {
  for (j in x) {
    vec1[i] <- sum(dnbinom(x = i, size = j, prob = 0.0044))
  }
}
vec1[which.max(vec1)]
which.max(vec1)
plot(vec1, x_vec)
for (j in x) {
  print(sum(dnbinom(550, j, prob = 0.01)))
}

library(MASS)
# Try the negative binomial model 
m21 <- glm(count ~ 1, data = rmdata, family = "negative")
m21
# Poisson model
m22 <- glm(count ~ 1, data = rmdata, family = poisson )
m22

model.comp <- 
  tibble(
    model=c('Negative Binomial','Poisson'),
    aic=c(AIC(m21), AIC(m22)), 
    `-2*loglik`=-2*c(logLik(m21), logLik(m22)),
    bic = c(BIC(m21), BIC(m22))
)
model.comp
